<paragraph blockId="28.[138,259,994,1018]" box="[138,259,994,1018]" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis box="[138,259,994,1018]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[138,1185,1042,1260]" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">
Length of fore wing: 
<emphasis box="[387,405,1044,1067]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">„</emphasis>
<quantity box="[414,501,1043,1067]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="28" pageNumber="191" unit="mm" value="26.0">26 mm</quantity>
; 
<specimenCount box="[515,529,1042,1067]" pageId="28" pageNumber="191" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
<quantity box="[537,626,1043,1067]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="28" pageNumber="191" unit="mm" value="27.0">27 mm</quantity>
. Very similar to the previous species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Warren)" baseAuthorityName="Warren" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Metallolophia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocellata">
<emphasis box="[1061,1185,1043,1067]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">M. ocellata</emphasis>
(Warren)
</taxonomicName>
. Frons and terminal part of palpus blackish brown. Abdominal crests almost without blackish hair. Wings, especially inner margin of hind wing, narrower and more elongate than 
<taxonomicName box="[302,382,1139,1163]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Metallolophia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocellata">
<emphasis box="[302,382,1139,1163]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">ocellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Fore wing with pale band below costa more conspicuous, hind wing with olive-green much extended along veins. Underside similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[951,1031,1172,1196]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Metallolophia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocellata">
<emphasis box="[951,1031,1172,1196]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">ocellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except that postmedian fascia on fore wing is rounded from costa to M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[862,873,1214,1230]" fontSize="7" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">3</subScript>
, then continuous to Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1166,1177,1214,1230]" fontSize="7" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">2</subScript>
, where it bends outwards and forms a distinct angle at its inner margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[138,1185,1319,1375]" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis box="[138,294,1319,1343]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[308,424,1319,1343]" captionStart="Figures 65–67" captionStartId="22.[138,207,1354,1373]" captionTargetBox="[194,1132,143,1302]" captionTargetId="figure-135@22.[183,1140,133,1318]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figures 65–67. Male genitalia; 68. female genitalia. (65) M. devecisi (ZSM G 789), (66) M. flavomaculata sp. nov., holotype (IZCAS Geom-00104). (67) M. stueningi sp. nov., paratype (IZCAS Geom-00340). (68) M. vitticosta (BMNH Geom-17129). Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5214624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5214624/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">Figure 65</figureCitation>
). Very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[726,848,1319,1343]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Metallolophia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocellata">
<emphasis box="[726,848,1319,1343]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">M. ocellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valva not narrowed towards apex; basal lobe of valva a little smaller.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[138,1184,1435,1523]" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis box="[138,318,1435,1459]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[333,451,1435,1459]" captionStart="Figures 75–78" captionStartId="24.[138,207,1315,1334]" captionTargetBox="[193,1132,141,1269]" captionTargetId="figure-47@24.[183,1140,133,1279]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figures 75–78. Female genitalia. (75) M. arenaria (BMNH Geom-20967). (76) M. cuneataria sp. nov., holotype (IZCAS Geom-00101). (77) M. inanularia sp. nov., holotype (IZCAS Geom-00102). (78) M. deveccisi (ZSM). Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5214628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5214628/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="191">Figure 78</figureCitation>
). Ductus bursae not clearly differentiated from corpus bursae, with a distinct sclerotized ring. Corpus bursae small and pyriform, with weakly sclerotized ridges on the posterior half.
</paragraph>
